main event: Unidentified flying object sighting in Ojibwa, Wisconsin on 15th May 1953, with conflicting data and no conclusive explanation.
interesting points: The observation lasted for 25 minutes, with the object traveling in an eastward direction.
There were no photographs or physical evidence obtained from the sighting.
The witness reported that the object traveled in a straight line at 120 mph and remained visible for 23 minutes, posing a contradiction.
The source of the report was civilians, namely Sand and Bill Olsen of Ojibwa, Wisconsin.
The conclusion of the report emphasized conflicting data and no changes were made at 1 year intervals, with reclassification after 12 years.
